    <p>
      <b class="big">It's a big country,</b> geographically and
      ideologically.  But given our current information revolution,
      one may have hoped that empathy and appreciation of different
      conditions and perspectives could benefit, and common
      understandings could emerge.  However, this revolution has also
      brought the seductive opportunity for each of us to more
      thoroughly surround and isolate ourselves in our own information
      bubble, fueled by the political and corporate media incentives
      to polarize.  Consequently, it appears the opposite may be
      happening.
    </p>

    <p>
      <b class="big">With Portrait of America at the Crossroads,</b>
      we hope to gain and share some understanding of the feelings,
      passions, and lives of people who don't ordinarily command a
      microphone.  In particular, our aim is towards unique and
      original perspectives and experiences, related to the issues and
      debates of our time, while doing our best to avoid simple
      recitations of the talking heads from our respective information
      bubbles.
    </p>

    <p>
      <b class="big">So thanks for visiting!</b> 
      Please take your time to browse the gallery (click on the
