    <h1>About Portrait of America at the Crossroads (PAX)</h1>

    <p>
      <b class="big">Talk with anyone</b> 
      who has lived through any presidential election in the past 60
      years, including 1968, and they will tell you that there is no
      precedent for what is taking place during the American election
      of 2016.
    </p>

    <p>
      <b class="big">Polarization,</b> real or perceived, of Democrat
      vs. Republican, liberal vs. conservative, privileged vs. the
      disempowered, consumes virtually nearly every political dialogue
      to an extent rarely seen.  Citizens on all sides express
      feelings of frustration of being left behind and without a
      voice.  Politicians and the media have cashed in by stoking the
      flames of misinformation, suspicions, and fear, inevitably
      cultivating to exagerated or irrational anger among voters, and
      leading to representatives incapable of compromise and governing.
    </p>

    <p>
      <b class="big">PAX intends to build bridges,</b> however slight,
      between the edges of these chasms, with an eye and ear toward
      the social and cultural rail of contemporary America.  PAX will
      look past the rhetoric spewing from the talking heads and
      instead look for unique and original stories and perspectives,
      as well as those commonly held hopes and values that reflect the
      passionate patriotism embraced by all sides.  Although our
      chasms of division are constantly being dug deeper by the power
      &amp; financial interests benefiting from them, the edges
      are not as far apart as we are led to believe.  Perhaps our
      bridges can provide a better angle to expose the diggers far
      below.
    </p>

    <p>
      <b class="big">We are</b> journalists, photographers, and
      technologists, committed to prividing an unflinching, unbiased
      view of the people we meet and events we encounter.  Watch this
      PAX gallery over the coming weeks and months for new scenes and
      stories, and follow us on 
      <a href="http://www.instagram.com/pax.gallery" target="_blank">Instagram</a> and
